column18: Probably washed in from ocean, looked healthy.
As at Kianninny yesterday, this Ecklonia is very heavily infested with parasites and growth. Perhaps it's a seasonal thing?

Most of the Ecklonia is covered with infestations of other algae this year, but it seems to be growing well in spite of this. 2 Years ago Council put in a new jetty and concreted posts, and we lost a lot of the macro algae so it's good to see it growing well this year.
I think the third image is a young Ecklonia plant?
